Ingredients:

    Boiled and mashed vegetables
    2 Big onions finely chopped
    2 Tomatoes Finley chopped
    1 tsp red chilli powder
    4 tsp Pav bhaji masala
    Salt to taste
    Oil 4 tsp
    2 tsp Ginger Garlic paste
    Butter
    Coriander leaves for garnishing

Method

    Heat oil in a pan. Once oil is hot add onions and fry till it gets slight golden color. Add ginger garlic paste and saute till raw smell from ginger garlic goes away.
    Then add tomatoes and cook till it gets fully mashed up. For this cook it covered for 3 to 4 mts.
    Now add pavbhaji masala and red chilli powder and saute till oil starts loosing out from the spices.
    Add mashed vegetables, sprinkle some salt, add water if required.
    Cover and cook for 5 mts
    Garnish with coriander leaves.
